# Tools Watchlist — Agent Rules

When Jon pastes a **GitHub/repo URL**, says **review tool**, **evaluate tool**, or **add to watchlist**:

## Canonical docs (Hermes-wide)

| Doc | Path |
|-----|------|
| Watchlist + grades | `D:\Hermes\projects\_core-scripts\shared-profile-content\docs\TOOLS-WATCHLIST.md` |
| Setup status (READY vs keys) | `...\docs\TOOLS-SETUP-STATUS.md` |
| Full research | `...\docs\TOOLS-REFERENCE.md` |

Execute [`.cursor/prompts/Review-Tool.md`](../prompts/Review-Tool.md) when a full review is requested.

## Policy (Jon 2026-07-04)

1. **Additive only** — never disable or replace working stack (Mem0, DeepSeek, ComfyUI, MCPs).
2. **Overlap OK** — strong alternatives on deck still earn ADOPT / IN USE.
3. **OSS/free first** — minimal paid OK when ROI is high.
4. **Install gate** — IN USE only after Jon approves (or says "run install now").

## Required outputs per review

1. Letter grade (A+→F) + score /100 + one-line summary
2. Verdict: IN USE | ADOPT | WATCH | SKIP
3. Setup status: READY | PARTIAL | NEEDS_KEY | NEEDS_LOGIN | NOT_INSTALLED
4. Update **shared canonical** docs (not JonBeatz-only copies unless syncing)
5. After install → run doctor/preflight → flip Setup to READY in TOOLS-SETUP-STATUS.md
6. Optional: `npm run draven:add -- "Tool X: grade, verdict, one line"`

## Quick status

Run `npm run tools:status` from any profile for config queue + counts.
